  "about": "Knowledge base of creative & development app project conventions. The backend reads this at build time to decide which files matter, which app owns them, and how to find a file's project root. To support a new tool, add an entry here — no Rust changes needed. Fields: name, icon, color (tailwind palette name), category, extensions (file types this app owns), structure ('nested' = projects contain deep subfolders, 'flat' = one document is the project), self_contained (true => the file's own folder IS the project; walking up is skipped), root_marker_exts (a folder is the project root if it directly contains a file with one of these extensions), root_marker_files (a folder is the project root if it directly contains a file/dir with one of these exact names), notes.",
